{#-
Community/hyperedge dossier page skeleton (Constitution III.13 / Amendment W).

Amendment D (read-only): a hyperedge is presented here, never mutated —
roster, formation-tick, and overlaps are display-only, no verb/mutation
affordance (design-canon S9: "hyperedge rendering is read-only presentation
and safe" while II.7 stays [TRANSITION STATE] for hyperedge MUTATION only).
Community is NEVER a graph node (II.7; MEMORY hex/community Lawverian
disposition) — this page projects from SocialClass.community_memberships,
never a node lookup.

Roster renders as [[social_class/<id>]] wikilinks — incidence-via-backlinks
(design-canon S9: "node pages list memberships; backlinks are incidence").
Overlaps render as [[community/<id>]] wikilinks to the sibling dossier.

Deliberately prose-free: this is a scaffold page, not narrative copy. Every
value interpolated here is either a plain string babylon.projection.vault.
render_community already resolved (statblock_rows/absent_fields — never a
raw Optional CommunityView field, for the same StrictUndefined-vs-"None"-
literal reason county.md.j2 documents) or a concrete, non-None entry drawn
directly from an already-filtered `if` guard (roster/overlaps members,
which are never None once the guard admits them).

Fenced directives only ({statblock}/{absence}), matching
babylon.tui.directives.BabylonFence dispatch (ADR099).
-#}
